text.paragraph:
If this product is used for 10 days or longer, intraocular pressure should be monitored even though it may be difficult in children and uncooperative patients (see 
                              WARNINGS
                           ).

Steroid Responsive Disease Treatment: Apply one to two drops of loteprednol etabonate ophthalmic suspension into the conjunctival sac of the affected eye(s) four times daily. During the initial treatment within the first week, the dosing may be increased, up to 1 drop every hour, if necessary. Care should be taken not to discontinue therapy prematurely. If signs and symptoms fail to improve after two days, the patient should be re-evaluated (see 
   PRECAUTIONS
).
